title: Add comprehensive tests for SKILL.md system
---
Add ~120 lines of new tests to test/test_skills.ml. All 19 existing test cases must remain unchanged and passing.

New test cases:
1. test_parse_frontmatter: Valid YAML frontmatter with name, description, allowed-tools, model. Verify key-value extraction and body separation.
2. test_parse_frontmatter_no_delimiters: Content without --- returns empty metadata list and full content as body.
3. test_skill_md_meta_of_frontmatter: Verify name+description required (None on missing), allowed-tools comma-split, model optional.
4. test_load_skill_md: Create temp dir with SKILL.md, load it, verify meta fields + instructions body.
5. test_load_skill_md_missing_name: SKILL.md without name field returns None.
6. test_substitute_arguments: '$ARGUMENTS' in body replaced with provided string. Multiple occurrences. No $ARGUMENTS = unchanged.
7. test_discover_md_skills: Create temp dir structure with skills in .claude-p/skills/ and .claude/skills/, verify discovery finds both, deduplicates by name (first-found wins).
8. test_use_skill_tool_found: Create temp skill, init cache, invoke use_skill tool with valid name, verify instructions returned.
9. test_use_skill_tool_not_found: Invoke with invalid name, verify error message lists available skills.
10. test_skill_md_priority: Same skill name in workspace and personal dirs — workspace version wins.
11. test_extract_skill_refs: '@review-and-fix' detected, '@unknown' not detected, email 'user@foo.com' not false-positive, multiple refs, dedup.
12. test_slash_command_skill: Slash_commands.handle ~skill_names:["foo"] "/foo bar" returns SkillInvoke("foo","bar"). /unknown returns NotACommand.
13. test_skill_list_tool_both_formats: Create temp dir with both a JSON skill file and a SKILL.md skill directory. Call skill_list_tool with workspace_dir. Verify output includes both JSON and SKILL.md skills with correct names/descriptions.

Acceptance criteria:
- All 13 new tests pass
- All 19 existing tests still pass
- make test passes
- make fmt-check passes